# 🚀 MERN Stack Bootcamp – Software Setup Guide

> ## ⚠️ Important
>
> Before attending the first bootcamp session, ensure that **all required software is installed and verified** on your computer.
>
> Completing this setup in advance will allow you to fully participate in the hands-on coding exercises from Day 1.

---

# 📦 Required Software and Tools

The following software is **mandatory** for all participants.

## 1️⃣ Visual Studio Code (VS Code)

**Purpose:** Source Code Editor

🔗 Download: https://code.visualstudio.com/

---

## 2️⃣ Node.js (LTS Version)

**Purpose:** JavaScript Runtime Environment

🔗 Download: https://nodejs.org/en/download

---

## 3️⃣ Git

**Purpose:** Version Control System

🔗 Download: https://git-scm.com/downloads

---

## 4️⃣ GitHub Account

**Purpose:** Code Hosting and Collaboration Platform

🔗 Create Account: https://github.com/

---

## 5️⃣ MongoDB Community Server

**Purpose:** NoSQL Database

🔗 Download: https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community

---

## 6️⃣ MongoDB Compass

**Purpose:** MongoDB GUI Tool

🔗 Download: https://www.mongodb.com/products/tools/compass

---

## 7️⃣ Postman

**Purpose:** API Development and Testing Tool

🔗 Download: https://www.postman.com/downloads/

---

## 8️⃣ Google Chrome

**Purpose:** Web Browser for Development and Testing

🔗 Download: https://www.google.com/chrome/

---

# 🛠️ Additional Recommended Tools

These tools are optional but strongly recommended for a smoother development experience.

### ✅ GitHub Desktop
Simplified graphical interface for Git and GitHub.

🔗 https://desktop.github.com/

### ✅ React Developer Tools
Inspect and debug React applications directly in the browser.

🔗 https://react.dev/learn/react-developer-tools

### ✅ Thunder Client
Lightweight API testing tool inside VS Code.

🔗 https://www.thunderclient.com/

### ✅ ESLint
Identify and fix JavaScript coding issues.

🔗 https://eslint.org/

### ✅ Prettier
Automatically formats your code according to industry standards.

🔗 https://prettier.io/

### ✅ 7-Zip
File compression and extraction utility.

🔗 https://www.7-zip.org/

---

# ✅ Installation Verification

After installation, open a terminal and run:

```bash
node -v
npm -v
git --version
```

Expected Output:

✔ Node.js Version Installed

✔ npm Installed

✔ Git Installed

